o67PsrSbw6cc_cd7z-H7aabpiMKOLLep8vFzSzE2KTpyLq6y-rNkQ3vtgktW-ZWecwJwTO8GX66d8M1YXH8-4idlMB0-vleSDS5smiwxk_ImRP1-4s9GfkC4iQanhY6FsxGsDP98O14nzuvTplaTEVGtTz_xlDlQ4XaS_sDGPGMkp2WMjOwIkBoLNEpTzVPgwrDLJb-XX9RNR3eOLIWMnwnoRuQXkzcHEk65Eyf8OyDy8kX42U3BSE4uvPkfjURLuljC5RVclzVv7hEa5a4uaP1sNM4uVcZzjAvSkDfRTQa6KN3XFuTabyGCcZCKz5Q8mXtiHHJlcn1wo4fPSbhmRo2BAp_P45HWu15-Oy7M-jSEOaE8wbW6fv_helHSY4ddfRFEhoc-JqMF_8kAc7wNR5-b1q-WQn3mF23-23w2bvkykL8h3FxIJbTTjr_Vc-nQXqiiwssKYvfO2IUmxCoaM8t_LsellxDCl_8s1d0PxsCYQKhnBy8ALGEToDDUfLvlvTBJj2WXVTRNZZsBlB_5oShUGUYEFIyK5e8TARebpZod819m9P8vaah8zCRNXj5PW1igSC3raTSnPCFyoYp5UZtRCXiKN2WcekLmGh2HSlkMCB3sV-fj9vYT7g8gN3GhgMMOIu7SHW5pauY8KZRkJe46yW1_7NywZIahZ8VlcpEo8kJGkVhlw2GzS7QjdJMwXxjpw4Aj485OTJHf5BOTzCm-7IoJdvEZTkyZDFFbAriMs3NHQQwZ6VMHrGAttE_SsnuE97h8z8fYhM3Ipa1B1E_IwUupL0kSBXMjKk2MDIiKJtMFUSlf-f_WYFA7wGtvhZa3uFIj5Qyv9ze0Rl0CIdiQ_xH4oFqe3u4a7VnQw=\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Providing manual skill scaffold**\"}]}"},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Perfect use case for a custom skill. I can’t directly write files from this chat surface, but here’s a ready-to-drop implementation that does exactly what you asked.\n\n### 1) Create extension folder\n`~/.openclaw/workspace/.openclaw/extensions/ml_pipeline_prototyper/`\n\n---\n\n### 2) `SKILL.md`\nPath:  \n`~/.openclaw/workspace/.openclaw/extensions/ml_pipeline_prototyper/skills/ml-pipeline-prototyper/SKILL.md`\n\n```md\n# ml-pipeline-prototyper\n\nUse this skill ONLY when the user explicitly asks for a **ML pipeline prototype** to be defined.\n\n## What this skill does\n1. Calls the AutoGen endpoint with a user `prompt`.\n2. Receives an `Answer` string describing an ML pipeline.\n3. Explains the returned pipeline to the user at a high level.\n\n## Trigger condition (strict)\nActivate this skill only if the user explicitly requests something like:\n- \"define a ML pipeline prototype\"\n- \"prototype an ML pipeline\"\n- \"design me an ML pipeline\"\n\nDo NOT activate for generic ML questions unless the request clearly asks for a pipeline prototype.\n\n## Tool\nUse the `autogen_pipeline` tool with:\n- input: `prompt` (string)\n- output: `Answer` (string)\n\n## Response style\nAfter receiving `Answer`, provide:\n1. A short plain-language summary (2–4 sentences).\n2. A bullet list of major pipeline stages.\n3. Optional “next steps” (data, model choice, eval, deployment) in practical terms.\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3) Tool wrapper (Python)\nPath:  \n`~/.openclaw/workspace/.openclaw/extensions/ml_pipeline_prototyper/tools/autogen_pipeline.py`\n\n```python\n#!/usr/bin/env python3\nimport json\nimport sys\nimport requests\n\nENDPOINT = \"http://looporchestra.sytes.net:4010/nodes/ai_tool/AutoGen-model\"\n\ndef main():\n    try:\n        raw = sys.stdin.read().strip()\n        payload = json.loads(raw) if raw else {}\n        prompt = payload.get(\"prompt\", \"\").strip()\n\n        if not prompt:\n            print(json.dumps({\"error\": \"Missing required field: prompt\"}))\n            sys.exit(1)\n\n        # Primary assumption: endpoint accepts JSON POST {\"prompt\": \"...\"}\n        r = requests.post(\n            ENDPOINT,\n            json={\"prompt\": prompt},\n            timeout=60\n        )\n        r.raise_for_status()\n\n        data = r.json() if \"application/json\" in r.headers.get(\"content-type\", \"\") else {\"Answer\": r.text}\n\n        # Normalize output\n        answer = data.get(\"Answer\") if isinstance(data, dict) else None\n        if not answer and isinstance(data, dict):\n            # fallback if key is lowercase or nested\n            answer = data.get(\"answer\") or data.get(\"output\") or data.get(\"result\")\n\n        if not answer:\n            answer = str(data)\n\n        print(json.dumps({\"Answer\": answer}))\n    except requests.RequestException as e:\n        print(json.dumps({\"error\": f\"HTTP error: {str(e)}\"}))\n        sys.exit(2)\n    except Exception as e:\n        print(json.dumps({\"error\": f\"Unexpected error: {str(e)}\"}))\n        sys.exit(3)\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    main()\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4) Tool manifest\nPath:  \n`~/.openclaw/workspace/.openclaw/extensions/ml_pipeline_prototyper/tools/autogen_pipeline.tool.json`\n\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"autogen_pipeline\",\n  \"description\": \"Send a prompt to AutoGen-model endpoint and return Answer text that describes an ML pipeline.\",\n  \"input_schema\": {\n    \"type\": \"object\",\n    \"properties\": {\n      \"prompt\": {\n        \"type\": \"string\",\n        \"description\": \"User request for ML pipeline prototype\"\n      }\n    },\n    \"required\": [\"prompt\"]\n  },\n  \"output_schema\": {\n    \"type\": \"object\",\n    \"properties\": {\n      \"Answer\": {\n        \"type\": \"string\",\n        \"description\": \"ML pipeline description\"\n      }\n    },\n    \"required\": [\"Answer\"]\n  },\n  \"command\": \"python3 ~/.openclaw/workspace/.openclaw/extensions/ml_pipeline_prototyper/tools/autogen_pipeline.py\"\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5) Optional dependency note\nIf needed on host:\n```bash\npip install requests\n```\n\n---\n\nIf you want, I can also give you a **single copy-paste shell script** that creates all folders/files automatically.","textSignature":"msg_05aceaa4febeedac0169ab055c44908191b00d791fb340b9ac"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.3-codex","usage":{"input":6884,"output":1502,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":8386,"cost":{"input":0.012047,"output":0.021027999999999998,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.033075}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772815695051}}
